<div class="intro">
  <h5>Rhyparography</h5>
  <h6>/ɹɪ.pəˈɹɒ.ɡɹə.fi/</h6>
  <p><em>(arts) The painting or literary depiction of mean or sordid things; especially still-life or genre painting. <br> From Ancient Greek ῥύπος (rhúpos, “filth”) +‎ -graphy.</em></p>
  <p>The aim is to emulate the vivid grotesquery of a <span><em><a href="https://www.google.com/search?q=spongebob+close+up" style="color:#fefcff">Spongebob Close Up</a></em></span>.<br>I delight in perverse, revolting, and hideous things because they express the beautiful absurdity and agonizing frustration of physical existence.</p>
  <p></p>
</div>

<div class="gallery">
  <div class="row">
    <% @filth.each do |f| %>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-6 col-md-3 col-lg-3">
        <div class="thumbnail">
          <a href="<%= f.url %>" target="_blank">
            <%= image_tag "#{f.url}", width: "cover"; %>
              <div class="caption">
                  <%= f.caption %>
              </div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>
  <ul class="list-inline">
    <li><%= link_to "Back", images_path, class: "btn-large" %></li>
    <li><%= link_to "Home", home_path, class: "btn-large" %></li>
  </ul>
</div>
